                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184.011102/198: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Albert Halstead</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-24T10:30:00+01:00"
                            >July 24, 1919—10:30 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 25—2 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>647. Your 137<note n="79" xml:id="d240fn79">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_613">p. 613</ref>.</note> not
                    received when telegram number (apparent omission) [646, July 24, 7 a.m.?] was
                    written. Will inform commission later in day extent to which wholly unofficial
                    negotiations proposed. I have not seen Boehm nor Bauer on the subject but have
                    acted through Cunningham and Commission is in no sense committed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Halstead</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
